div.h1: Interrupt Stack Frame: What the CPU Pushes
div.h3: Complete Stack State After Interrupt Delivery

div.p: Stack grows downward Lower addresses at top

g.title: Handler: pusha (skipped ESP - uses old value)
User Stack Segment - CPU pushed (privilege change)
User Stack Pointer - CPU pushed (privilege change)
Processor flags (IF cleared for interrupt gate)
pusha saves ESP but it's the kernel ESP

div.p: *Error code only present for certain exceptions struct cpu_state offset calculations use these values

ol.li: ESP, SS (only if returning to lower privilege) This is why privilege transitions work automatically!

ul.li: Saves user SS:ESP on kernel stack TSS must be configured before any user-mode code runs!

div.p: Only these exceptions push error code:

ul.li: 21 (Control Protection) IRQs (32-47) never push error code

div.p: pusha pushes: DI, SI, BP, SP, BX, DX, CX, AX The saved SP is the value before pusha executed (original ESP - 16) popa restores all except SP
